Sentencas: A fundamental understanding of oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) is essential for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, following our previous studies of protonic ceramic fuel cell (PCFCs) cathode material, CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure composite material is used as an air electrode over oxide ion conducting electrolyte ceramic fuel cell.
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: CaFe2O4-WO3 as a cathode over Sm-doped CeO2 (SDC) electrolyte exhibits a very low area-specific resistance (ASR) of 0.18 Omega cm(2) and excellent power output of 842 mW-cm(-2) at 500 degrees C. The CaFe2O4-WO3 cathode showed improved electrochemical performance in LT-SOFC compared to PCFCs
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent ORR activity of CaFe2O4-WO3 could mainly be assisted with the superficial release of oxygen ions than the protons with enhanced incorporation abilities through the interface of CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure.
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, engineering the heterostructure by forming complex oxidation states at the interface of CaFe2O4-WO3 narrows the band gap.
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: It can effectively facilitate small polaron hopping of valence electrons and diffusion of oxygen ions, resulting in high electrical conductivity and electrocatalyst function in SOFCs.
Titulo: Experiencing heightened oxygen reduction response in CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure for ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, various spectroscopic and density functional calculations are employed to catch the understanding of CaFe2O4-WO3 heterostructure composite as a new functional ORR electrocatalysts for advanced LT-SOFCs.
